@Raheem Aslam  I'm pretty sure Sonic would rather eat chili dogs than exercise lmao. And no, my channel is not a parody. I'm simply a fan of Sonic Underground. Something that other people refuse to believe actually exist and shit... You see, I was bullied as a kid for liking SU, so I decided to be the one to put my talents to work and prove those bitches wrong and that Sonic Underground is deserving of more credits than it is given.
It's ironic. The show is about being a good person and treating others how you wish to be treated, but most people tend to act likle the evil Dr. Robotnik these days and try to force their opinion on others, and people eat it upthose false claims just because the majority of people say them. News flash, just because more people believe something, it doesn't mean it's the correct way of thinking.
